{
  "text": "Prophylaxis with itraconazole (200 mg daily) was effective in patients with CD4 cell counts <150 cells/mm3 in areas where the incidence of histoplasmosis is >10 cases per 100 patient-years. [CITATION_1] Itraconazole can reduce the frequency of histoplasmosis, although not mortality, in patients who have advanced HIV infection and who live in areas where histoplasmosis is highly endemic. [CITATION_2] However, incidence >10 cases/100 only occurs during outbreaks in the United States. [CITATION_3] The incidence may be above 10% in some Latin American countries, but cost may be prohibitive. If prophylaxis is implemented, it can be discontinued in patients on antiretroviral treatment once CD4 counts are \u2265150 cells/mm 3 for 6 months. Prophylaxis should be restarted if the CD4 count falls to <150 cells/mm 3 .",
  "correct_citation": {
